    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ §8 EDGE CASES -->
    <div class="dp-section" id="edge-cases">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§8</div>
        <h2>System Rules &amp; Edge Cases</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="dp-flow">
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Invalid Signature</h4>
          <p>signature_status = "invalid". btnValApproveSign disabled. Bulk approve skips this session. Both lblValSigBadge and lblValPropSigResult show red badge. ValidationEvent sig_verified written with details: { result: "invalid" }. Reject and Flag remain available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Duplicate Serial — Double Spend</h4>
          <p>duplication_status = "duplicate". lblValDoubleSpendBadge → red "✗ DOUBLE SPEND DETECTED". btnValApproveSign disabled. Note auto-flagged if risk_score below HIGH RISK threshold. Cannot be bulk-approved. High-visibility warning in evidence panel.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Registry Mismatch</h4>
          <p>Serial exists in registry but issuer/denomination/asset_code don't match the submitted note. registry_verified = false; duplication_status = "duplicate" (conservative). Approve blocked; warning in evidence panel.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Missing Manifest</h4>
          <p>manifest_hash is null after ingest. IngestService creates session with parse_warning. signature_status auto-set to "unknown" — cannot verify without payload hash. Risk score +10 applied. Operator must reject or flag; cannot approve.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Risk Score ≥ 75</h4>
          <p>Session auto-flagged at ingest. Appears under "Flagged" filter immediately. btnValApproveSign shows override confirmation dialog — not disabled, but requires explicit acknowledge of HIGH RISK. Excluded from all bulk approve operations without exception.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Network Failure</h4>
          <p>Verify / Approve / Reject / Flag / Freeze: show QMessageBox; no state change on client; no partial writes; operator retries manually. Import: per-file error shown; other files unaffected. Inbox auto-refresh: silent failure; retries on next 30-second tick.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Multi-Sig Threshold</h4>
          <p>required_approvals &gt; 1: first approval appends to approval_chain but does not set final_decision. Session remains Pending visually. txtValEvMultiSig shows "{n} / {required}". Only when threshold met: final_decision = approved + settlement triggered.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Partial Batch Approval</h4>
          <p>Each session independently approved/rejected — no system-level batch lock. lblValBatchProgress tracks processed count vs total. A batch is "complete" only when all sessions have a final_decision.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ §9 E2E FLOW -->
    <div class="dp-section" id="flow">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§9</div>
        <h2>End-to-End Flow</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="dp-flow">
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Import</h4>
          <p>rdoValImportFile → btnValImportCBDC → QFileDialog. For each PNG: magic byte check (89 50 4E 47) → chunk iteration (tEXt/zTXt/iTXt) → key=value parse → denomination symbol stripped → risk score computed → ValidationSession created → image copied to storage/validation_images/{ref}_obverse.png → session_ref returned. m_tableCleared = false; loadQueue() fires.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Signature Verification</h4>
          <p>Operator clicks row → onRowSelected() → populateEvidencePanel() + populatePropertiesTab() + populatePreview(). Operator clicks btnValVerifySignature → POST verify_signature → 3-step issuer key match (exact → strip parens → SQL prefix) → Base64URL decode sig → hex decode payload_hash → RbNaCl Ed25519 verify → signature_status updated → badges refresh.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Registry Lookup</h4>
          <p>btnValRegistryLookup → GET registry_lookup/{serial} → CbdcNote queried → duplication_status set (unique or duplicate) → Liquidity &amp; Trade section populated with lock_id, coverage_status, corridor_cap, trade_claim_id → btnValApproveSign enabled only when both unique + sig valid.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Risk Review</h4>
          <p>Risk applied automatically at ingest. Operator reviews prgValRiskScore (colour-coded bar), lblValRiskLevel, lblValRiskFlags. Properties tab shows individual flag breakdown in Risk Profile page and lblValPropRiskBadge summary.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Operator Review</h4>
          <p>Three layers: (1) Security Evidence — signature badge, double-spend badge, note details, liquidity context. (2) Validation Properties QToolBox — Technical Manifest, Compliance History, Risk Profile. (3) CBDC Preview — visual inspection of obverse + reverse banknote images with metadata.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Decision</h4>
          <p>Approve: btnValApproveSign (sig=valid + dup=unique required; risk≥75 needs override). Reject: cmbValRejectReason required → btnValRejectNote. Flag: btnValFlagInvestigation + optional reason. Freeze: btnValFreezeNote — immediate, no reason, locks system-wide.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Ledger Update</h4>
          <p>On approval: final_decision = approved; CbdcNote.status = active; approval_chain appended; if required_approvals threshold met → settlement triggered + LiquidityLock.used_amount += denomination + corridor utilization updated. On rejection: CbdcNote.status = rejected; no ledger credit. On freeze: CbdcNote.status = frozen; governor action required to unfreeze.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="dp-step">
          <h4>Audit Trail</h4>
          <p>Every step creates an immutable ValidationEvent. event_types: ingested | sig_verified | registry_checked | approved | rejected | flagged | frozen | exported. Accessible via btnValViewAuditTrail animated drawer, txtValEventLog timeline, or btnValExportLog export. No UPDATE or DELETE ever permitted on ValidationEvent records.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

